## 2026-03-29 - ImportPanel conflict-detection failure is invisible
- Added `existingTokenMapError` state to track fetch failures. In `.catch()`, now calls `setExistingTokenMapError(message)` alongside `setExistingTokenMap(null)`. Error is cleared on new fetch start and on cache-hit path. Updated the preview summary JSX to show "Conflict detection unavailable" warning (with the error message as a `title` tooltip) when `existingTokenMapError !== null`, and updated the visibility condition to include the error state so the warning area renders even when `previewNewCount` is null.
